{"nodes":[{"content":"How to select and configure the Device Fundamentals tests","pos":[0,57]},{"content":"The WDK for Windows 8 provides a driver testing framework that includes a set of tests called the Device Fundamentals tests.","pos":[201,325]},{"content":"The Device Fundamentals tests are a collection of tests that are used both internally at Microsoft for testing the drivers and driver samples that ship with Windows and the WDK, and externally as part of the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Certification Program for Hardware<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?linkid=8705)</ept>.","pos":[326,626],"source":" The Device Fundamentals tests are a collection of tests that are used both internally at Microsoft for testing the drivers and driver samples that ship with Windows and the WDK, and externally as part of the [Windows Certification Program for Hardware](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?linkid=8705)."},{"content":"You can run the tests from your development environment.","pos":[627,683]},{"content":"When you run the tests, you can use the same parameters that are used for Windows Certification testing, or you can configure and customize the run-time parameters according to your testing and debugging needs.","pos":[684,894]},{"pos":[1106,1157],"content":"Getting the most from the Device Fundamentals tests"},{"content":"To get the most benefit from the Device Fundamentals tests, your device must be supported by the default I/O plug-ins.","pos":[1421,1539]},{"content":"To see whether your device type is supported and to determine whether there are specific requirements for testing, refer to <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Provided WDTF Simple I/O plug-ins<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Hh781398)</ept>.","pos":[1540,1768],"source":" To see whether your device type is supported and to determine whether there are specific requirements for testing, refer to [Provided WDTF Simple I/O plug-ins](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Hh781398)."},{"content":"The Device Fundamentals test also include a utility you can use to test your device to see whether it is supported.","pos":[1769,1884]},{"content":"If your device is not supported, you can create a WDTF Simple I/O plug-in.","pos":[1885,1959]},{"content":"in Visual Studio.","pos":[1960,1977]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>How to customize I/O for your device using the WDTF Simple I/O Action Plug-in<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Hh706277)</ept>.","pos":[1978,2152],"source":" For more information, see [How to customize I/O for your device using the WDTF Simple I/O Action Plug-in](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Hh706277)."},{"pos":[2316,2351],"content":"About the Device Fundamentals Tests"},{"content":"The WDK provides the Device Fundamentals tests in two configurations, Basic and Certification.","pos":[2551,2645]},{"content":"In both configurations, you can edit the test parameters to vary the length of the test, the number of test cycles to perform, and other test parameters, depending upon how you want to test the targeted devices or drivers.","pos":[2646,2868]},{"content":"The Basic configuration is intended for general driver and device testing and debugging.","pos":[2869,2957]},{"content":"Use the Basic configuration early on and throughout the development cycle.","pos":[2958,3032]},{"content":"The tests in the Basic configuration have the same settings that are used in the Windows Certification testing, with the exception of having a shorter run time.","pos":[3033,3193]},{"content":"In the Certification configuration, the tests have the same settings that are used in the Windows Certification testing.","pos":[3194,3314]},{"content":"Use the Certification configuration to verify readiness for testing your device or driver for the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Certification Program for Hardware<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?linkid=8705)</ept>.","pos":[3315,3505],"source":" Use the Certification configuration to verify readiness for testing your device or driver for the [Windows Certification Program for Hardware](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?linkid=8705)."},{"pos":[3507,3649],"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Device Fundamentals Tests<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/JJ673011)</ept> include tests in the following categories.","source":"The [Device Fundamentals Tests](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/JJ673011) include tests in the following categories."},{"content":"CHAOS Tests (Device Fundamentals)","pos":[3656,3689]},{"content":"Coverage Tests (Device Fundamentals)","pos":[3764,3800]},{"content":"CPUStress Tests (Device Fundamentals)","pos":[3875,3912]},{"content":"Driver Install Tests (Device Fundamentals)","pos":[3987,4029]},{"content":"I/O Tests (Device Fundamentals)","pos":[4104,4135]},{"content":"Penetration Tests (Device Fundamentals)","pos":[4210,4249]},{"content":"PNP Tests (Device Fundamentals)","pos":[4324,4355]},{"content":"Reboot Tests (Device Fundamentals)","pos":[4430,4464]},{"content":"Sleep Tests (Device Fundamentals)","pos":[4539,4572]},{"content":"Utility","pos":[4647,4654]},{"content":"Driver Verifier","pos":[4677,4692]},{"pos":[4880,4916],"content":"Setting the run-time test parameters"},{"content":"You can edit the run-time parameters for many of the Device Fundamentals tests.","pos":[4918,4997]},{"content":"In the Driver Test Group window, an arrow (») next to a test name indicates that the test has parameters that you can change.","pos":[4998,5123]},{"content":"Click the arrow (») to display the run-time parameters.","pos":[5124,5179]},{"content":"One of the most useful parameters is <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>DQ<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>, which specifies the target device to test.","pos":[5181,5266],"source":"One of the most useful parameters is *DQ*, which specifies the target device to test."},{"content":"The default value (<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IsDevice<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>) tests all of the devices on the target computer.","pos":[5267,5348],"source":" The default value (**IsDevice**) tests all of the devices on the target computer."},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>DQ<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> parameter takes a <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt><bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>WDTF<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept><ept id=\"p2\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Ff539547)</ept> <bpt id=\"p4\">[</bpt>SDEL<ept id=\"p4\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Ff539571)</ept> query that identifies the target devices.","pos":[5349,5571],"source":" The *DQ* parameter takes a [**WDTF**](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Ff539547) [SDEL](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Ff539571) query that identifies the target devices."},{"content":"You can specify a particular device for testing, for example:","pos":[5572,5633]},{"pos":[5635,5747],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>DeviceID=’USB\\\\ROOT\\_HUB\\\\4&amp;1CD5D022&amp;0’<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> selects only the device for testing with the specified <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>DeviceID<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","source":"**DeviceID=’USB\\\\ROOT\\_HUB\\\\4&1CD5D022&0’** selects only the device for testing with the specified **DeviceID**."},{"pos":[5749,5875],"content":"For more information about <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>DQ<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> and the other run-time parameters, see <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Device Fundamentals test parameters<ept id=\"p2\">](#DevFund_Params)</ept>.","source":"For more information about *DQ* and the other run-time parameters, see [Device Fundamentals test parameters](#DevFund_Params)."},{"pos":[5976,6011],"content":"Device Fundamentals Test Parameters"},{"content":"Parameter","pos":[6264,6273]},{"content":"Description","pos":[6296,6307]},{"content":"DQ","pos":[6419,6421]},{"content":"Identifies the device or devices that should be used for testing.","pos":[6456,6521]},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;em&gt;</ph>DQ<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/em&gt;</ph> parameter takes a <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Ff539547\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</ph>WDTF<ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Ff539571\"&gt;</ph>SDEL<ph id=\"ph5\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph> query that identifies the target devices.","pos":[6522,6785],"source":" The <em>DQ</em> parameter takes a <a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Ff539547\"><strong>WDTF</strong></a><a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Ff539571\">SDEL</a> query that identifies the target devices."},{"content":"This query can be very flexible and it can be used to express any number of devices, from a single device to all devices in the system.","pos":[6786,6921]},{"content":"Common examples:","pos":[6929,6945]},{"content":"To test all devices that were installed with a specific INF File:","pos":[7219,7284]},{"content":"INF::FileName=<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;</ph>INF_File_Name","pos":[7305,7345],"source":"INF::FileName=</strong><em>INF_File_Name"},{"content":"For example, <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>INF::OriginalInfFileName='%InfFileName%'","pos":[7358,7419],"source":"For example, <strong>INF::OriginalInfFileName='%InfFileName%'"},{"content":"This is the default value.","pos":[7436,7462]},{"content":"To test a device with a specific Device Id:","pos":[7666,7709]},{"content":"DeviceId=’<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;</ph>DeviceId<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</ph>’","pos":[7731,7776],"source":"DeviceId=’</strong><em>DeviceId</em><strong>’"},{"content":"For example, <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>DeviceID=’USB\\ROOT_HUB\\4<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;amp;</ph>1CD5D022<ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;amp;</ph>0’","pos":[7793,7858],"source":"For example, <strong>DeviceID=’USB\\ROOT_HUB\\4&amp;1CD5D022&amp;0’"},{"content":"To test a device with a specific interface:","pos":[8072,8115]},{"content":"Interfaces::<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;</ph>InterfaceGUID","pos":[8136,8174],"source":"Interfaces::</strong><em>InterfaceGUID"},{"content":"To test a device with a specific driver letter:","pos":[8392,8439]},{"content":"Volume::DriverLetter=’<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;</ph>DriveLetter<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</ph>’","pos":[8460,8520],"source":"Volume::DriverLetter=’</strong><em>DriveLetter</em><strong>’"},{"content":"For example, <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>Volume::DriverLetter=’c:\\’","pos":[8537,8584],"source":"For example, <strong>Volume::DriverLetter=’c:\\’"},{"content":"To test a device with a specific driver:","pos":[8794,8834]},{"content":"DriverBinaryNames=<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;</ph>mydriver.sys","pos":[8856,8899],"source":"DriverBinaryNames=</strong><em>mydriver.sys"},{"content":"To test all device of a specific device Class:","pos":[9181,9227]},{"content":"For example, <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>Class=CDROM<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> would test all device of class CDROM.","pos":[9241,9320],"source":"For example, <strong>Class=CDROM</strong> would test all device of class CDROM."},{"content":"For example, <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>ClassGUID= {36fc9e60-c465-11cf-8056-444553540000}<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> would test all the devices whose class GUID matches the specified GUID.","pos":[9328,9479],"source":"For example, <strong>ClassGUID= {36fc9e60-c465-11cf-8056-444553540000}</strong> would test all the devices whose class GUID matches the specified GUID."},{"content":"In this case, the GUID is for the USB class.","pos":[9480,9524]},{"content":"DoPoolCheck","pos":[9684,9695]},{"content":"True or False.","pos":[9730,9744]},{"content":"Monitors the driver's use of the paged and nonpaged system memory pools by using pool tags and lookaside lists.","pos":[9745,9856]},{"content":"This option also monitors changes in the number of exceptions handled which might indicate errors in exception handling.","pos":[9857,9977]},{"content":"ChangeBufferProtectionFlags","pos":[10172,10199]},{"content":"True or False.","pos":[10234,10248]},{"content":"Changes the memory protection flags of buffers passed to the tested device.","pos":[10249,10324]},{"content":"The memory protection flags alternates between no access, read-only, and read-only with page guard.","pos":[10325,10424]},{"content":"DoSimpleIO","pos":[10569,10579]},{"content":"True or False.","pos":[10614,10628]},{"content":"Runs SimpleI/O (if found) on test devices before and after performing PNP operations.","pos":[10629,10714]},{"content":"DoConcurrentIO","pos":[10870,10884]},{"content":"True or False.","pos":[10919,10933]},{"content":"Uses <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Ff539547\"&gt;</ph>WDTF<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph> concurrent I/O interface to send I/O requests to target device stacks while performing PnP operations.","pos":[10934,11127],"source":" Uses <a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/Library/Windows/Hardware/Ff539547\">WDTF</a> concurrent I/O interface to send I/O requests to target device stacks while performing PnP operations."},{"content":"FillZeroPageWithNull","pos":[11302,11322]},{"content":"True or False.","pos":[11357,11371]},{"content":"Maps the zero page and fills it with NULL values.","pos":[11372,11421]},{"content":"This test identifies drivers that do not verify a pointer reference before dereferencing the pointer.","pos":[11422,11523]},{"content":"FuzzTestPeriod","pos":[11679,11693]},{"content":"Fuzz test period in minutes.","pos":[11728,11756]},{"content":"HPU","pos":[11858,11861]},{"content":"Specifies the high processor utilization percentage.","pos":[11896,11948]},{"content":"Impersonate","pos":[12095,12106]},{"content":"True or False.","pos":[12141,121